row.hDescrLong:
HANDLE
Developer: David B Pigman Date: 02/16/2010 The new Security Matrix Report projectretains the same functionality of the existing project, fixes existing problems with omissions of data and provides several additional security views for use with PeopleSoft query. - Code fixes have been implemented to resolve this issue with omissions of data - Several additional security reporting views have been provided to resolve complex security data for use in reporting. - Security information is provided real-time. All logic is embedded in security views. If there is a concern of the queries degrading performance, the project also provides the option of resolving security data in two tables by the execution of the same SMCSECMT SQR batch job scheduled to run each night.
A file path must be specified in the run control Do not specify the file name. The path should be in the format of Enter Path as "\\<Server Name>\<Directory>\". PeopleSoft must have access to this directory path in order to work. Two files will be created. Simply cust and past to open in Excel.
